{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}} {{family name hatnote|Katakura|lang=Japanese}} [[Image:Kuyo.svg|thumb|right|140px|The emblem ([[:en:Mon (badge)|''mon'']]) of the Katakura clan]] The {{nihongo|'''Katakura clan'''|片倉氏|Katakura-shi}} is a Japanese family which claims its descent from [[:en:Fujiwara no Toshihito|Fujiwara no Toshihito]] by way of [[Katō Kagekado]]. The family entered [[:en:Mutsu Province|Mutsu Province]] in the 14th century as subordinates of the [[Ōsaki clan]]. However, in 1532, they became retainers of the [[:en:Date clan|Date clan]], and remained so until 1872. In the [[:en:Sengoku era|Sengoku era]], the Katakura took part in all the major campaigns of the Date clan. The family's head, [[:en:Katakura Kagetsuna|Katakura Kagetsuna]], became renowned throughout the country, even receiving praise from [[Toyotomi Hideyoshi]], who granted Kagetsuna a fief (thereby bypassing Kagetsuna's status as vassal to [[:en:Date Masamune|Date Masamune]]).
In the Edo period, the heads of the Katakura clan were hereditary ''[[:en:Karō|Karō]]'' in the [[:en:Sendai Domain|Sendai Domain]]. Their personal fief was centered at [[Shiroishi Castle]] (modern-day [[Shiroishi, Miyagi]]).
[[Shigenobu Katakura]], the current chief priest of Sendai's [[Aoba Shrine]], is a direct descendant of this family.
==Head Family== # Katakura Kagekatsu # Katakura Kagefusa # Katakura Kagenobu # Katakura Kageharu # Katakura Kagetsune # Katakura Kagetoki # Katakura Kageshige # Katakura Kagesuke # Katakura Kageyuki # Katakura Kagehiro # Katakura Kagemura # Katakura Kageshige # [[:en:Katakura Kagetsuna|Katakura Kagetsuna]] # [[:en:Katakura Shigenaga|Katakura Shigenaga]] # [[:en:Katakura Kagenaga (2nd)|Katakura Kagenaga (2nd)]] # [[:en:Katakura Muranaga|Katakura Muranaga]] # [[:en:Katakura Murayasu|Katakura Murayasu]] # [[:en:Katakura Muranobu|Katakura Muranobu]] # [[:en:Katakura Murasada|Katakura Murasada]] # [[:en:Katakura Murakiyo|Katakura Murakiyo]] # [[:en:Katakura Muratsune|Katakura Muratsune]] # [[:en:Katakura Kagesada|Katakura Kagesada]] # [[:en:Katakura Munekage|Katakura Munekage]] # [[:en:Katakura Kuninori|Katakura Kuninori]] # [[:en:Katakura Kagenori|Katakura Kagenori]] # [[:en:Katakura Kagemitsu|Katakura Kagemitsu]] # [[:en:Katakura Kenkichi|Katakura Kenkichi]] # [[:en:Katakura Nobumitsu|Katakura Nobumitsu]] # [[Shigenobu Katakura]]
== Others == * [[:en:Katakura Kita|Katakura Kita]] (1538-1610) was the half-sister of Katakura Kagetsuna and teacher of Date Masamune and Kagetsuna.
